message.text:
Spring is just around the corner! 
Have you ever heard of the so-called SAKURA ZENSEN 桜前線, or CHERRY BLOOMING FORECAST?
The Japan Meteorological Agency records the opening and full bloom of the cherry blossoms across the Japanese islands. 
In ancient Japan, cherry blossoms were regarded as an important sign to forecast how crops would grow in the coming year. 
This weekend seems to be the best timing to go cherry blossom viewing in Tokyo area!
If you find our SAKURA SISTERS, namely Yoshino-chan, Sato-chan, and Yae-chan enjoying their time of the year, be sure to let us know! :)
http://marugotoweb.jp/cast_and_characters.php
